As Disc (Link 2) roll without slipping on Link 1 (surface) so their I-centre of rotation lies on point of contact to avoid relative motion in between them. So [latex]\mathrm{I}_{12}[/latex] lies on point of contact. Link 2 and 3 have instantaneous center of rotation at [latex]\mathrm{I}_{13}[/latex] due to fixed surface of Link 1. As per point Plies on link 2 and 3 both so, point [latex]P[/latex] has same velocity for Link 2 and 3 both. As per Kennedy's theorem, if three plane bodies have relative motion among themselves, their I-centre must lie on a straight line. So, [latex]\mathrm{I}_{23}[/latex] must be on line joining [latex]\mathrm{I}_{13}[/latex] and [latex]\mathrm{I}_{12}[/latex] at point P. By similar [latex]\triangle \mathrm{PI}_{12} \mathrm{~B}[/latex] and [latex]\Delta \mathrm{Pl}_{13} \mathrm{~A}[/latex], we have [latex]
\frac{\mathrm{l}_{12} \mathrm{P}}{\mathrm{l}_{12} \mathrm{~B}}=\frac{\mathrm{Pl_{13 }}}{\mathrm{PA}}
[/latex] or, [latex]\quad \frac{\mathrm{I}_{12} \mathrm{I}_{23}}{2}=\frac{\mathrm{I}_{23} \mathrm{l}_{13}}{8}[/latex] or,

[latex]
\mathrm{I}_{12} \mathrm{l}_{13}=0.25 \mathrm{I}_{23} \mathrm{l}_{13} \;\;\;...(i)
[/latex] Velocity of point [latex]P[/latex] is same w.r.t. all instantaneous rotation so, [latex]
\omega_{1} \times I_{12} I_{23}=\omega_{2} \times I_{23} l_{13}
[/latex] By equation (i), we get [latex]
\omega_{2}=0.25 \omega_{1}
[/latex]

Given [latex]
R+r=30 \quad \text {...(i) }
[/latex] [latex]\frac{T_{1}}{T_{2}}=\frac{1}{4} ; \quad[/latex] where [latex]T=[/latex] no. of teeth or

[latex]
\mathrm{T}_{2}=4 \mathrm{T}_{1}
[/latex] Diametrical pitch [latex]=\frac{8 \text { teeth }}{\mathrm{mm}}=\frac{\mathrm{T}}{\mathrm{D}}=\mathrm{P}_{\mathrm{d}}[/latex] and

[latex]
m=\frac{D}{T}=\frac{1}{P_{d}}
[/latex] As,

[latex]
\begin{aligned}
r & =\frac{m T}{2} \\
R & =\frac{m T_{2}}{2}, r=\frac{m T_{1}}{2}
\end{aligned}
[/latex] by equation (i) we have [latex]
\frac{m T_{2}}{2}+\frac{m T_{1}}{2}=30
[/latex] or, [latex]\frac{m}{2}\left(T_{1}+T_{2}\right)=30[/latex] or, [latex]\frac{1}{8 \times 2}\left(T_{1}+T_{2}\right)=30[/latex] As

[latex]
\mathrm{T}_{2}=4 \mathrm{T}_{1}
[/latex] So, [latex]\frac{1}{16}\left(T_{1}+4 T_{1}\right)=30[/latex] or

[latex]
\sigma_{1}=\frac{30 \times 16}{5}=96
[/latex]

Since the disc is in pure rolling on the string By rotating the disc with angle [latex] \theta[/latex]  results in rotating the rod with angle [latex] \beta[/latex]  (let us say) about hinge point. Now for same deflectionof point ' [latex] B[/latex]  ' [latex] 
\begin{aligned}
L \beta & =r \theta \\
\beta & =\frac{r \theta}{L} \quad \because r=\frac{L}{4} \\
\beta & =\frac{L}{4} \frac{\theta}{L}
\end{aligned}
[/latex] By energy method Total energy, [latex] 
\begin{aligned}
& \mathrm{E}_{\text {total }}=\frac{1}{2} \mathrm{I}_{\mathrm{p}} \dot{\theta}^{2}+\frac{1}{2} \mathrm{k}(2 \mathrm{r} \theta)^{2}+\frac{1}{2} 2 k\left(\frac{\mathrm{L}}{2} \beta\right)^{2} \\
& \mathrm{E}_{\text {total }}=\frac{1}{2} I_{p} \dot{\theta}^{2}+\frac{1}{2} k(2 r \theta)^{2}+k\left(\frac{L}{2} \frac{\theta}{4}\right)^{2} \\
& \frac{\mathrm{dE}_{\text {total }}}{\mathrm{dt}}=0 \\
& =\frac{1}{2} \times \frac{3}{2} \mathrm{mr}^{2} \times 2 \dot{\theta} \ddot{\theta}+\frac{1}{2} \mathrm{k} \times 4 \mathrm{r}^{2} \times 2 \theta \dot{\theta}+\frac{k L^{2}}{64} \times 2 \theta \dot{\theta}=0 \\
& \frac{3 m}{2} \frac{L^{2}}{16} \ddot{\theta}+\frac{4 L^{2}}{16} k \theta+\frac{2}{64} k L^{2} \theta=0 \\
& \left(\frac{3 m}{32}\right) \ddot{\theta}+\left(\frac{9 k}{32}\right) \theta=0 \\
& 3 m \ddot{\theta}+9 k \theta=0 \\
& \ddot{\theta}+\left(\frac{3 k}{m}\right) \theta=0 \\
& \omega_{n}=\sqrt{3} \sqrt{\frac{k}{m}}
\end{aligned}
[/latex]
